5000|$|In March 2010, State Rep. Linda Harper-Brown filed House Bill 2719. House Bill 2719 {{would allow}} Amazon to avoid Texas sales tax by {{amending}} the state tax code to <b>exempt</b> <b>companies</b> or individuals from being classified as retailers or being ordered to provide state agencies {{with information on}} purchases made in Texas, if they make use of [...] "only a fulfillment center...or computer server." [...] House Bill 2719 stands {{in sharp contrast to}} House Bill 2403, introduced by Rep. John Otto. House Bill 2403 would close loopholes in the Texas tax code that support Amazon's claim of being exempt from collecting sales tax.|$|R
